ic diameters in the experiment\nand simulation, respectively, exceeding typical lengths of microfluidic\ndesigns. Our work highlights the key role of transient cell distribution in\ndilute suspensions, which may negatively affect the reliability of experimental\nresults if not taken into account.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Aug 2019 08:01:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 May 2020 14:47:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-08"}
